				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">What you mean by &quot;data selector&quot; is what I meant by &quot;buffer IC&quot;. The address lines alone would need 39 pins (13 from CPU, 13 from PPU, 13 out to RAM), plus a bunch more for select lines. It'd have to latch the data bus too in order to satisfy the CPU's setup and hold timing if it services a read from the CPU close to a read from the PPU. So with the majority of the cart bus as well as all RAM signals, you're looking at a minimum close to 80 pins.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

